header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Server/Test/Runner.html#Lean.Server.Test.Runner.waitForMessage\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Server</span>.<span class=\"name\">Test</span>.<span class=\"name\">Runner</span>.<span class=\"name\">waitForMessage</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">msg</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#String\">String</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Data/Lsp/Ipc.html#Lean.Lsp.Ipc.IpcM\">Lsp.Ipc.IpcM</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Unit\">Unit</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Waits for a `textDocument/publishDiagnostics` notification with a specific message to be emitted.\nDiscards all received messages, so should not be combined with `Ipc.collectDiagnostics`. Used to\nimplement the `waitFor` test directive.\n\nIf the server reports a `$/lean/fileProgress` notification with `fatalError` kind, this aborts\nwith an error rather than blocking forever: the message we are waiting for will never be\nproduced (the worker either crashed or its header processing failed fatally, so no body\nelaboration will run).\n\nKept here rather than in `Lean.Lsp.Ipc` because it is specifically a test-driver helper rather\nthan a general-purpose IPC primitive.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Server/Test/Runner.html#Lean.Server.Test.Runner.waitForMessage","kind":"def","line":485,"name":"Lean.Server.Test.Runner.waitForMessage","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Server/Test/Runner.lean#L485-L517"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Server/Test/Runner.html#Lean.Server.Test.Runner.processSync\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Server</span>.<span class=\"name\">Test</span>.<span class=\"name\">Runner</span>.<span class=\"name\">processSync</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Server/Test/Runner.html#Lean.Server.Test.Runner.RunnerM\">RunnerM</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Unit\">Unit</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Server/Test/Runner.html#Lean.Server.Test.Runner.processSync","kind":"def","line":479,"name":"Lean.Server.Test.Runner.processSync","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Server/Test/Runner.lean#L479-L483"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Server/Test/Runner.html#Lean.Server.Test.Runner.processWaitForILeans\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Server</span>.<span class=\"name\">Test</span>.<span class=\"name\">Runner</span>.<span class=\"name\">processWaitForILeans</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Server/Test/Runner.html#Lean.Server.Test.Runner.RunnerM\">RunnerM</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Unit\">Unit</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Server/Test/Runner.html#Lean.Server.Test.Runner.processWaitForILeans","kind":"def","line":474,"name":"Lean.Server.Test.Runner.processWaitForILeans","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Server/Test/Runner.lean#L474-L477"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Server/Test/Runner.html#Lean.Server.Test.Runner.processCollectDiagnostics\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Server</span>.<span class=\"name\">Test</span>.<span class=\"name\">Runner</span>.<span 